markdown: This report outlines the analysis of various drivers impacting the Key Performance Indicator (KPI). The analysis utilized Pearson and Spearman correlation methods to assess the relationships between the drivers and the KPI. The results indicate that all drivers exhibit weak correlations with the KPI and none are statistically significant. This suggests that the drivers analyzed may not be the primary factors influencing the KPI, and further investigation may be required to identify more impactful variables.
